{"title_page": "1981 Grand Prix (tennis)", "text_new": "{{ Infobox tennis circuit season\n<!-- Details -->\n| name          = 1981 Grand Prix circuit\n| image         = Ivan Lendl (1984) cropped.jpg\n| image_caption = Ivan Lendl at 1984.\n| image_alt     = \n| image_size    = 200px\n| duration      = January 5, 1981 \u2013 January 17, 1982\n| edition       = 12th\n| tournaments   = 89\n| categories    = [[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] (4) <br/> Grand Prix (74) <br/> [[World Championship Tennis]] (9) <br/> Team Events (2)\n<!-- Achievements -->\n| most_tournament_titles       = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] (9)\n| most_tournament_finals       = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] (15)\n| prize_money_leader           = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] ($991,000)\n| points_leader                = {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Ivan Lendl]] (1571)\n<!-- Awards -->\n| player_of_the_year            = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]]\n| most_improved_player_of_the_year = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Peter McNamara]]\n| newcomer_of_the_year             = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Mayotte]]\n| comeback_player_of_the_year      = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Jeff Borowiak]]\n| previous = [[1980 Grand Prix (tennis)|1980]]\n| next     = [[1982 Grand Prix (tennis)|1982]]\n}}\nThe '''1981 Volvo Grand Prix''' was the only men's professional [[tennis]] circuit held that year. It consisted of the four [[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] tournaments and the [[Grand Prix tennis circuit|Grand Prix]] tournaments. The [[World Championship Tennis]] (WCT) Tour was incorporated into the Grand Prix circuit. The WCT tour consisted of eight regular tournaments, a season's final, three tournaments categorized as special events and a doubles championship. In total 89 tournaments were held divided over 29 countries. The circuit was administered by the [[Men's International Professional Tennis Council]] (MIPTC).\n\n==Schedule==\nThe table below shows the '''1981 Volvo Grand Prix schedule''' (precursor to the [[ATP Tour]]).\n\n