2| [[Auckland]], New Zealand <br> Hard \u2013 $75,000 \u2013 32S/16D\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Wilkison]] <br> 6\u20134, 6\u20134, 6\u20134\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Russell Simpson (tennis)|Russell Simpson]]\n| rowspan=2| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Robert Van't Hof]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Chris Mayotte]]\n| rowspan=2| {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Chris Lewis (tennis)|Chris Lewis]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Matt Mitchell (tennis player)|Matt Mitchell]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Lloyd Bourne]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Larry Stefanki]]\n|-valign=top\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Jonathan Smith (tennis)|Jonathan Smith]] <br> {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Andrew Jarrett]] <br> 7\u20135, 7\u20136\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Larry Stefanki]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Robert Van't Hof]]\n\n|-valign=top\n|rowspan=2 style=\"background:#ffc\"|[[1981 Volvo Masters|Volvo Masters]]<BR> Masters [[New York City|New York]], U.S.<br> Carpet \u2013 $400,000 \u2013 S12/D6\n| {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Ivan Lendl]]<BR> 6\u20137<sup>(5\u20137)</sup>, 2\u20136, 7\u20136<sup>(8\u20136)</sup>, 6\u20132, 6\u20134.\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Vitas Gerulaitis]]\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Eliot Teltscher]]<BR>{{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]]\n|rowspan=2| <center>Round Robin</center>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Roscoe Tanner]]<BR>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Jimmy Connors]]<BR>{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Guillermo Vilas]]<BR>{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Clerc]]\n|-valign=top\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Peter Fleming (tennis)|Peter Fleming]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] <br> 6\u20133, 6\u20133\n| {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Kevin Curren]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Steve Denton]]\n|}\n\n==Points system==\nThe tournaments listed above were divided into twelve point categories. The highest points were allocated to the Grand Slam tournaments; French Open, the Wimbledon Championships, the US Open and the Australian Open. Points were allocated based on these categories and the finishing position of a player in a tournament. The points table is based on a 32 player draw. No points were awarded to first-round losers and advancements by default were equal to winning a round.<ref>{{cite book|title=Slazengers World of Tennis 1982 : the official yearbook of the International Tennis Federation|year=1982|publisher=Queen Anne Press|location=London|isbn=9780356085968|page=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_0356085961/page/26 26]|edition=14th|editor=John Barrett|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_0356085961/page/26}}</ref>  The points allocation, with doubles points listed in brackets, is as follows:\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n!width=100|\n!width=80|Grand Slam\n!width=80|$300,000+\n!width=80|$275,000+\n!width=80|$250,000+\n!width=80|$225,000+\n!width=80|$200,000+\n!width=80|$175,000+\n!width=80|$150,000+\n!width=80|$125,000+\n!width=80|$100,000+\n!width=80|$75,000+\n!width=80|$50,000+\n|-\n|Winner || 350 (70) || 300 (60) || 275 (55) || 250 (50) || 225 (45) || 200 (40) || 175 (35) || 150 (30) || 125 (25) || 100 (20) || 75 (15) || 50 (10)\n|-\n|Runner-up || 245 (49)|| 210 (42) || 192 (38) || 175 (35) || 157 (31) || 140 (28) || 122 (24) || 104 (20) || 87 (17) || 70 (14) || 52 (10) ||  35 (7)\n|-\n|Semifinalist || 140 (28) || 120 (24) || 110 (22) || 100 (20) || 90 (18) || 80 (16) || 70 (14) || 60 (12) || 50 (10) || 40 (8) || 30 (6) || 20 (4) \n|-\n|Quarterfinalist || 70 (14) || 60 (12) || 55 (11) || 50 (10) || 45 (9) || 40 (8) || 35 (7) || 30 (6) || 25 (5) || 20 (4) || 15 (3) || 10 (2)\n|-\n|Fourth round || 35 (7) || 30 (6) || 27 (6) || 25 (5) || 22 (5) || 20 (4) || 17 (3) || 14 (3) || 12 (2) || 10 (2) || 7 (\u2013) || 5 (\u2013)\n|-\n|Third round || 17 (3) || 15 (\u2013) || 13 (\u2013) || 12 (\u2013) || 11 (\u2013) || 10 (\u2013) || 9 (\u2013) || 7 (\u2013) || 6 (\u2013) || 5 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013)\n|-\n|Second round || 9 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013) || \u2013 (\u2013)\n|}\n\n==Grand Prix standings==\n\n1. [[Ivan Lendl]] (Cze)\n\n2. [[John McEnroe]] (USA)\n\n3. [[Jimmy Connors]] (USA)\n\n4. [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Clerc]] (Arg)\n\n5. [[Guillermo Vilas]] (Arg)\n\n6. [[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]] (Sue)\n\n7. [[Roscoe Tanner]] (USA)\n\n8. [[Eliot Teltscher]] (USA)\n\n9. [[Vitas Gerulaitis]] (USA)\n\n10. [[Yannick Noah]] (Fra)\n\n<ref>http://www.tenniscom.com/setlectura/grandprix.htm</ref>\n\n==ATP rankings==\n{| \n|- valign=\"top\"\n||\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" | As of January 1981\n|-\n! Rk \n! width=\"200\" | Name\n! width=\"60\" | Nation\n|-valign=top\n| 1\n| [[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}}\n|-valign=top\n| 2\n| [[John McEnroe]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 3\n| [[Jimmy Connors]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 4 \n| [[Gene Mayer]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 5\n| [[Guillermo Vilas]]\n| {{flagicon|ARG}}\n|-valign=top\n| 6\n| [[Ivan Lendl]]\n| {{flagicon|TCH}}\n|-valign=top\n| 7\n| [[Harold Solomon]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 8\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Clerc]]\n| {{flagicon|ARG}}\n|-valign=top\n| 9\n| [[Vitas Gerulaitis]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} \n|-valign=top\n| 10\n| [[Eliot Teltscher]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 11\n| [[Brian Gottfried]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 12\n| [[Brian Teacher]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 13\n| [[Eddie Dibbs]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} \n|-valign=top\n| 14\n| [[Roscoe Tanner]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 15\n| [[Wojciech Fibak]]\n| {{flagicon|POL}}\n|-valign=top\n| 16\n| [[John Sadri]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top\n| 17\n| [[Victor Amaya]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}}\n|-valign=top}\n| 18\n| [[Johan Kriek]]\n| {{flagicon|RSA|1928}}\n|-valign=top\n| 19\n| [[Bal\u00e1zs Tar\u00f3czy]]\n| {{flagicon|HUN}}\n|-valign=top\n| 20\n| [[Vijay Amritraj]]\n| {{flagicon|IND}}\n|}\n||\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" | Year-end rankings (January 1982) \n|- valign=\"top\"\n! Rk \n! width=\"200\" 