alva]] Napa\n*{{flagicon|ECU}} [[Andr\u00e9s G\u00f3mez]] Bordeaux\n*{{flagicon|IND}} [[Ramesh Krishnan]] Manila\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Mel Purcell]] Tampa\n*{{flagicon|TCH}} [[Pavel Slo\u017eil]] Nancy\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thierry Tulasne]] B\u00e5stad\n\n==See also==\n* [[World Championship Tennis]]\n* [[1981 WTA Tour]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* ATP Archive 1981 [https://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/results-archive?year=1981 Volvo Grand Prix Tournaments]\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book | title=The Bud Collins History of Tennis: An Authoritative Encyclopedia and Record Book|last= Collins|first= Bud|authorlink= Bud Collins | publisher=New Chapter Press |location= New York | edition= 2nd |year=2010|isbn= 978-0-942257-70-0 }}\n\n{{ATP seasons}}\n{{1981 Volvo Grand Prix}}\n{{1981 in tennis}}\n{{Mens tennis seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Grand Prix tennis circuit seasons]]\n[[Category:1981 Grand Prix (tennis)| ]]\n[[Category:1981 in tennis|Grand Prix]]\n", "text_old": "{{ Infobox tennis circuit season\n<!-- Details -->\n| name          = 1981 Grand Prix circuit\n| image         = Ivan Lendl (1984) cropped.jpg\n| image_caption = Ivan Lendl at 1984.\n| image_alt     = \n| image_size    = 200px\n| duration      = January 5, 1981 \u2013 January 17, 1982\n| edition       = 12th\n| tournaments   = 89\n| categories    = [[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] (4) <br/> Grand Prix (74) <br/> [[World Championship Tennis]] (9) <br/> Team Events (2)\n<!-- Achievements -->\n| most_tournament_titles       = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] (9)\n| most_tournament_finals       = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] (15)\n| prize_money_leader           = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] ($991,000)\n| points_leader                = {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Ivan Lendl]] (1571)\n<!-- Awards -->\n| player_of_the_year            = {{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]]\n| most_improved_player_of_the_year = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Peter McNamara]]\n| newcomer_of_the_year             = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Mayotte]]\n| comeback_player_of_the_year      = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Jeff Borowiak]]\n| previous = [[1980 Grand Prix (tennis)|1980]]\n| next     = [[1982 Grand Prix (tennis)|1982]]\n}}\nThe '''1981 Volvo Grand Prix''' was the only men's professional [[tennis]] circuit held that year. It consisted of the four [[Grand Slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] tournaments and the [[Grand Prix tennis circuit|Grand Prix]] tournaments. The [[World Championship Tennis]] (WCT) Tour was incorporated into the Grand Prix circuit. The WCT tour consisted of eight regular tournaments, a season's final, three tournaments categorized as special events and a doubles championship. In total 89 tournaments were held divided over 29 countries. The circuit was administered by the [[Men's International Professional Tennis Council]] (MIPTC).\n\n==Schedule==\nThe table below shows the '''1981 Volvo Grand Prix schedule''' (precursor to the [[ATP Tour]]).\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===January===\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:95%\n! style=\"width:48px;\"|Week\n! style=\"width:248px;\"|Tournament\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Champions\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Runners-up\n! style=\"width:190px;\"|Semifinalists\n! style=\"width:190px;\"|Quarterfinalists\n\n|-valign=top\n| rowspan=4| 19 Jan\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"| [[1981 Monterrey WCT|Monterrey WCT]] <br/> [[Monterrey]], Mexico <br> Super Series <br> Carpet \u2013 $200,000 \u2013 32S/16D\n| {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Johan Kriek]] <br> 7\u20136, 3\u20136, 7\u20136\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Vitas Gerulaitis]]\n| rowspan=2| {{flagicon|IND}} [[Vijay Amritraj]] <br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Wojciech Fibak]]\n| rowspan=2| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Bruce Manson]] <br> {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Pascal Portes]] <br> {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Ra\u00fal Ram\u00edrez]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[John Sadri]]\n|-valign=top\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Steve Denton]] <br> {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Kevin Curren]] <br> 7\u20136, 6\u20133\n\n| {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Kevin Curren]]\n|-valig