lagicon|TCH}} [[Pavel Slo\u017eil]] (1) Nancy\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Roscoe Tanner]] (1) Philadelphia\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Bal\u00e1zs Tar\u00f3czy]] (3) Monte Carlo, Hilversum, Tokyo Outdoor\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Brian Teacher]] (1) Columbus\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Eliot Teltscher]] (2) Puerto Rico, San Francisco\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thierry Tulasne]] (1) B\u00e5stad\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Vince Van Patten]] (1) Tokyo Indoor\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Robert Van't Hof]] (1) Taiwan\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Guillermo Vilas]] (3) Mar del Plata, Cairo, Houston\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Mark Vines]] (1) Bercy\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Wilkison]] (1) Sydney Outdoor\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Van Winitsky]] (1) Hong Kong\n\nThe following players won their first title in 1981:\n*{{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Kevin Curren]] Johannesburg\n*{{flagicon|AUS}} [[John Fitzgerald (tennis)|John Fitzgerald]] Kitzb\u00fchel\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Sammy Giammalva]] Napa\n*{{flagicon|ECU}} [[Andr\u00e9s G\u00f3mez]] Bordeaux\n*{{flagicon|IND}} [[Ramesh Krishnan]] Manila\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Mel Purcell]] Tampa\n*{{flagicon|TCH}} [[Pavel Slo\u017eil]] Nancy\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thierry Tulasne]] B\u00e5stad\n\n==See also==\n* [[World Championship Tennis]]\n* [[1981 WTA Tour]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* ATP Archive 1981 [https://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/results-archive?year=1981 Volvo Grand Prix Tournaments]\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book | title=The Bud Collins History of Tennis: An Authoritative Encyclopedia and Record Book|last= Collins|first= Bud|authorlink= Bud Collins | publisher=New Chapter Press |location= New York | edition= 2nd |year=2010|isbn= 978-0-942257-70-0 }}\n\n{{ATP seasons}}\n{{1981 Volvo Grand Prix}}\n{{1981 in tennis}}\n{{Mens tennis seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Grand Prix tennis circuit seasons]]\n[[Category:1981 Grand Prix (tennis)| ]]\n[[Category:1981 in tennis|Grand Prix]]\n", "name_user": "Wolbo", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eJanuary 1982:Tiebreak form